    return em.find(Order.class, id);
  }
}
```

## Additional Information

In addition to updating the import statement and annotation, we also need to update the `pom.xml` file to use the Jakarta EE API instead of the Java EE API. This can be done by replacing the `javax.ejb` dependency with `jakarta.ejb`.

For example, if the `pom.xml` file contains the following dependency:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>javax.ejb</groupId>
  <artifactId>javax.ejb-api</artifactId>
  <version>3.2</version>
</dependency>
```

It should be replaced with:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>jakarta.ejb</groupId>
  <artifactId>jakarta.ejb-api</artifactId>
  <version>4.0</version>
</dependency>
```

Note that the version number may vary depending on the specific Jakarta EE version being used.
